Meet the guides behind the Gut Health Reset 🤍

This programme is held by practitioners who deeply understand that gut health is never just about food.

It’s about the nervous system.
It’s about safety.
It’s about rhythms, habits, and feeling supported — not fixed.

Each guide brings their own lens, expertise, and lived experience, and together they create a container that feels informed, human, and genuinely nourishing.

@theseed_coaching brings a calm, steady presence to the reset, supporting the body through structure, rhythm, and nervous-system awareness. Her work gently bridges physiology and lived experience, helping change feel both safe and sustainable.

@elinapavlidis brings the wisdom of Tibetan medicine into the reset, offering a holistic view of digestion that considers energy, constitution, and balance. Her guidance invites a slower, more attuned relationship with the body — where symptoms are listened to, not rushed.

@aleholisticdining brings food back to its rightful place: nourishing, practical, and joyful. Her approach is rooted in functional nutrition while remaining deeply intuitive, making everyday choices feel accessible rather than overwhelming.

@flaviadeuchler weaves the reset together through a holistic lens that honours body, mind, and context. With a background in functional medicine and transformational coaching, she holds the container, keeping the work grounded, integrative, and human.

If you’re curious about who will be walking alongside you in this reset, this is your invitation to meet them.

🔗 Link in bio to learn more.

#oracollective #guthealthreset #holisticguthealth #integrativehealth #nervoussystemsupport

